**Claim:** Competition from immigrant workers benefits consumers and raises the overall standard of living.
**Purpose:** propose => Competition from immigrant workers benefits consumers and raises the overall standard of living.;
**Content:** Yes, some native-born workers might be affected.  As a professor, I face competition from foreign-born PhDs. This might impact my wages, but it benefits students who receive a more affordable education. The same principle applies across all sectors: competition from immigrant workers benefits consumers. Focus on production: when it doubles, everyone’s standard of living rises. This isn’t trickle-down; it’s Niagara Falls economics.
